Director JHT:
I never had any intention of casting Jisoo. It was hard to imagine how Youngro would be in real life, but I thought that the actor would complete the character. I never planned on hiring a rookie actor.
As soon as I saw out Jisoo, I thought “That person is Youngro”

JHI was the actor who had the most scenes with me. JHI took care of me really well. And we did character analysis together (?) I was able to act enjoyably because all the seniors monitored together and they gave me tips as well.
It was my first acting challenge so i was very nervous and anxious but I felt that I was really Youngro and everyone took care of me so I was able to film well.

What kind of acting can we expect from JHI in this drama?
My acting is my acting, but many actors come out in this drama. I showed a new side through this drama and learned many things. I wonder how it will show up on screen. I think the memories will stay with me a long time
“Snowdrop is a flower that blooms through the snow. If you hold on a little longer, spring will come”
Director Jo Hyun Tak said filming was very difficult, to the point of dying. But during that time thanks to JHI and KJS filming was enjoyable.

Jisoo read the script the first time before auditioning and she felt she was a bright and charming character and wanted to deliver the brightness and energy to people. While acting as Youngro she learned many things.
